    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-07-31T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-07-31T10:00:00-05:00" n="45"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d45">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/34</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW2"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gerard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Berlin</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-31T16:00:00+01:00">
                        <hi rend="italic">July 31, 1914, 4 p.m.</hi>
                    </date>
                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received, 2:36 p.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                <p>In my opinion Russia’s mobilization makes war inevitable. Probable Germany will
                    ask United States to take over embassies and <pb facs="0338" n="24"
                        xml:id="pg_24"/> interests Russia, France, and perhaps others. Do you
                    assent? Thousands of Americans in Germany. Food prices already doubled. Suggest
                    your sending navy despatch boat <hi rend="italic">Hamburg</hi> for emergencies
                    and load that boat and another with food supplies for Americans only. Also
                    consider question of sending German boats with American passengers from German
                    ports under international agreement might bring gold from American friends to
                    Americans stranded here.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GJW2">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Gerard</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
